{
  "text": "No dog had inducible AV nodal reentrant tachycardia. Causes anesthetized OAVRT rates in our study, they are faster than in a previously reported group of 14 dogs, in which the anesthetized OAVRT rate was 229 AE 42 bpm. 34 Whereas focal atrial tachycardias (FAT) had faster ventricular rates than OAVRT in that study, median OAVRT rate in our awake dogs was substantially higher and median OAVRT rate in our anesthetized dogs was the same as the anesthetized mean FAT ventricular rate (278 bpm) in the prior study. Isoflurane can affect AV conduction as well as atrial, ventricular, and AP refractory periods. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Significant prolongation of the P 0 R interval and lesser prolongation of the R 0 P interval in the anesthetized state versus the unmedicated, awake state (Table 3) was seen in our group of dogs.",
